# Copy to .env (gitignored). NEVER commit real secrets.
# The app is fully on-device — no cloud parse tier, no sign-in — so it needs
# no EXPO_PUBLIC_* values of its own. The entries below configure the unused
# backend/supabase proxy code kept in the repo for a possible future opt-in
# sync (see docs/design/pure-local-build-spec.md).

# --- Backend / proxy only (do NOT expose to the app) ---
# Only the model key is a real secret. The parse function uses the auto-injected
# SUPABASE_URL + SUPABASE_ANON_KEY (low privilege) to verify the caller's JWT —
# it deliberately does NOT use the RLS-bypassing service-role key.
# ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=

# Abuse/cost controls for the parse proxy (Upstash Redis, REST API). Without
# these the function FAILS OPEN (no rate limit / quota) — set them in prod.
# UPSTASH_REDIS_REST_URL=
# UPSTASH_REDIS_REST_TOKEN=
# Optional tuning (defaults shown): per-user daily parses (free tier; users fall
# back to manual entry beyond it), per-IP req/min, cache TTL.
# AI_DAILY_QUOTA=5
# AI_RATE_LIMIT_PER_MIN=20
# AI_CACHE_TTL_SECONDS=86400
